<p>Peoples&#8217; Council accused as perpetrator and receives terror attack since December 2008, 
including threat with a weapon, death threats, defamation in the mass media, and police 
detention. He was detained on 7 April for 24 hours after the police accused him involved on the 
series of violences in Jayapura during general election in Indonesia, but released soon after the 
police cannot find any evidences.    
